rbnL2tpMib.name: rbnL2tpMib

revisions.description: Added new table rbnL2tpPeerTunCfgTable. Updated the compliance statements and groups to reflect the change.

Added new objects rbnL2tpTCfgRemoteTunnelID and rbnL2tpTCfgTunnelContext to rbnL2tpTunnelCfgEntry. Added new NOTIFICATION-TYPE rbnL2tpMibTunnelStateChange2. Deprecated rbnL2tpMibTunnelTrapContext, rbnL2tpMibTunnelTrapState, and rbnL2tpMibTunnelStateChange. Updated the compliance statements and groups to reflect the changes.

rbnL2tpMib.contactinfo: RedBack Networks, Inc. Postal: 300 Holger Way San Jose, CA 95134 USA Phone: +1 408 750 5000 Fax: +1 408 750 5599 E-mail: mib-info@redback.com
rbnL2tpMib.description: Defines the objects necessary to monitor L2TP configuration information, counters and the state changes of an L2TP tunnel. All mib objects defined in the module are viewed within the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in the v1/v2 or the contextName in v3).

rbnL2tpPeerCfgEntry.name: rbnL2tpPeerCfgEntry
rbnL2tpPeerCfgEntry.description: An L2TP Peer Information entry. An entry in this table corresponds to the resources assigned to a single peer configuration. This configuration will be inherited by all of the tunnels that are assigned to the peer group. Entries are added to the table once communication is established with the peer. Entries are removed if communication is lost.

rbnL2tpMibPeerName.name: rbnL2tpMibPeerName
rbnL2tpMibPeerName.description: This object identifies the name of the Peer on the local system. This peer is the name of an identifier for a tunnel configuration and each tunnel that is assigned to this peer will take on the peer's configuration parameters.

rbnL2tpPCfgMedia.name: rbnL2tpPCfgMedia
rbnL2tpPCfgMedia.description: This object identifies the transport media utilized between communicating peers. A media length of 0 means that no transport media type was set.

rbnL2tpPCfgVendor.name: rbnL2tpPCfgVendor
rbnL2tpPCfgVendor.description: This object identifies the vendor of L2TP stack running on the remote peer. The length of the string will be zero if no vendor name can be obtained from the peer.

rbnL2tpPCfgRev.name: rbnL2tpPCfgRev
rbnL2tpPCfgRev.description: This object identifies the firmware revision for the L2TP protocol stack running on the remote peer.

rbnL2tpPCfgHostName.name: rbnL2tpPCfgHostName
rbnL2tpPCfgHostName.description: This object identifies the name assigned to this peer on the remote host system. A host name length of 0 means that this information could not be obtained from the remote host.

rbnL2tpPCfgRadius.name: rbnL2tpPCfgRadius
rbnL2tpPCfgRadius.description: This object indicates whether or not a RADIUS server has been configured for this peer group. A value of true (1) indicates that there is a RADIUS server and it will be used for authenticating and authorizing access to a tunnel in this group and accounting information will be sent to the radius server. A value of false (2) indicates that there is no RADIUS server and authentication and authorization will be done locally.

rbnL2tpPCfgRemIPAddType.name: rbnL2tpPCfgRemIPAddType
rbnL2tpPCfgRemIPAddType.description: This object identifies the address type contained in rbnL2tpPCfgRemIPAdd.

rbnL2tpPCfgRemIPAdd.name: rbnL2tpPCfgRemIPAdd
rbnL2tpPCfgRemIPAdd.description: This object identifies the remote IP address for this tunnel (utilized only with User Datagram Protocol).

rbnL2tpPCfgStatic.name: rbnL2tpPCfgStatic
rbnL2tpPCfgStatic.description: This objects indicates whether the tunnel is static or dynamic. A value of true (1) means that it is static. A value of (2) indicates that it is dynamic.

rbnL2tpPCfgLocalIPAddType.name: rbnL2tpPCfgLocalIPAddType
rbnL2tpPCfgLocalIPAddType.description: This object identifies the address type contained in rbnL2tpPCfgLocalIPAdd.

rbnL2tpPCfgLocalIPAdd.name: rbnL2tpPCfgLocalIPAdd
rbnL2tpPCfgLocalIPAdd.description: This object indicates the local IP address for this tunnel (utilized only with UDP).

rbnL2tpPCfgMode.name: rbnL2tpPCfgMode
rbnL2tpPCfgMode.description: This object indicates whether the peer is operating as an LNS, a LAC, or both.

rbnL2tpPCfgMaxTunnels.name: rbnL2tpPCfgMaxTunnels
rbnL2tpPCfgMaxTunnels.description: This object indicates the maximum number of tunnels that may be configured on this peer.

rbnL2tpPCfgMaxSesPerTun.name: rbnL2tpPCfgMaxSesPerTun
rbnL2tpPCfgMaxSesPerTun.description: This object indicates the maximum number of sessions that may be allocated to one tunnel.

rbnL2tpPCfgCtlRetranCnt.name: rbnL2tpPCfgCtlRetranCnt
rbnL2tpPCfgCtlRetranCnt.description: This object indicates a count of the number of times that a control packet was retransmitted.

rbnL2tpPCfgCtlRetranTO.name: rbnL2tpPCfgCtlRetranTO
rbnL2tpPCfgCtlRetranTO.description: This object indicates the control retransmit timeout in seconds.

rbnL2tpPCfgSessAuth.name: rbnL2tpPCfgSessAuth
rbnL2tpPCfgSessAuth.description: This object indicates the session authentication type.

rbnL2tpPCfgCtlWin.name: rbnL2tpPCfgCtlWin
rbnL2tpPCfgCtlWin.description: This object indicates the control window size.

rbnL2tpPCfgDNIS.name: rbnL2tpPCfgDNIS
rbnL2tpPCfgDNIS.description: This object indicates whether the critera used for a tunnel switch is Dialed Number Identification String first (a value of (1)), DNIS only (a value of (2)) or the no preference has been set (a value of (0)).

rbnL2tpPCfgPoliceRate.name: rbnL2tpPCfgPoliceRate
rbnL2tpPCfgPoliceRate.description: This object indicates the received aggregate stream limit, in kilobits per second.

rbnL2tpPCfgPoliceBurst.name: rbnL2tpPCfgPoliceBurst
rbnL2tpPCfgPoliceBurst.description: This object indicates the packet burst tolerance for tunnels received by this peer group.

rbnL2tpPCfgLimitRate.name: rbnL2tpPCfgLimitRate
rbnL2tpPCfgLimitRate.description: This object indicates the limit of the aggregate packet stream transmitted through a tunnel in kilobits per second (kpbs).

rbnL2tpPCfgLimitBurst.name: rbnL2tpPCfgLimitBurst
rbnL2tpPCfgLimitBurst.description: This object indicates the the packet burst tolerance limit transmitted on a tunnel.

rbnL2tpPCfgGroup.name: rbnL2tpPCfgGroup
rbnL2tpPCfgGroup.description: This object indicates the l2tp group which is assigned to this peer. Each peer configuration may be assigned only one tunnel group. A length of 0 means that the group name was not assigned.

rbnL2tpPCfgPref.name: rbnL2tpPCfgPref
rbnL2tpPCfgPref.description: This object indicates the RADIUS based preference number (used by tunnel groups only). A lower number indicates a more favorible preference.

rbnL2tpPCfgPasswd.name: rbnL2tpPCfgPasswd
rbnL2tpPCfgPasswd.description: This object indicates the password for this account utilized when performing the connection handshake protocol with the remote host. A length of 0 indicates that no password has been assigned.

rbnL2tpPCfgHelloTimer.name: rbnL2tpPCfgHelloTimer
rbnL2tpPCfgHelloTimer.description: This object defines the interval (in seconds) in which Hello (or keep-alive) packets are to be sent by local tunnels belonging to this tunnel configuration.

rbnL2tpPCfgRecQue.name: rbnL2tpPCfgRecQue
rbnL2tpPCfgRecQue.description: This object indicates whether there is receive queueing of out of sequence messages. A value of true (1) indicates that the messages are queued.

rbnL2tpPCfgSessContext.name: rbnL2tpPCfgSessContext
rbnL2tpPCfgSessContext.description: This object indicates the name of the session context. A size of 0 indicates that the context could not be determined. Any context name length greater than 80 will be truncated. This will have a value for PPPoE only.

rbnL2tpPCfgSessService.name: rbnL2tpPCfgSessService
rbnL2tpPCfgSessService.description: The service group to which this session belongs. A length of 0 indicates that no service group was assigned.

rbnL2tpPCfgEthEncap.name: rbnL2tpPCfgEthEncap
rbnL2tpPCfgEthEncap.description: This object indicates the ethernet encap type.

rbnL2tpPCfgEthSession.name: rbnL2tpPCfgEthSession
rbnL2tpPCfgEthSession.description: This object indicates the ethernet session of which this is a part. This is only set for non PPPoE sessions otherwise it will have a zero length.

rbnL2tpPCfgTunnelCount.name: rbnL2tpPCfgTunnelCount
rbnL2tpPCfgTunnelCount.description: This object indicates the number of tunnels that are active for this peer configuration.

rbnL2tpPCfgTunCtlErrs.name: rbnL2tpPCfgTunCtlErrs
rbnL2tpPCfgTunCtlErrs.description: This object is a count of the number of tunnel control errors encountered by tunnels connected to this peer.

rbnL2tpPCfgSessionCount.name: rbnL2tpPCfgSessionCount
rbnL2tpPCfgSessionCount.description: This object is a count of the number of sessions that are part of this peer.

rbnL2tpTunnelCfgEntry.name: rbnL2tpTunnelCfgEntry
rbnL2tpTunnelCfgEntry.description: An L2TP Tunnel Information entry. An entry in this table corresponds to a single tunnel. Entries are added to this table as tunnels become connected. Entries are removed from the table if the communication with one or both ends of a tunnel is lost.

rbnL2tpMibTunnelID.name: rbnL2tpMibTunnelID
rbnL2tpMibTunnelID.description: This object indicates the ID number of this tunnel.

rbnL2tpTCfgTunnelNm.name: rbnL2tpTCfgTunnelNm
rbnL2tpTCfgTunnelNm.description: This object indicates the local name that was given to this tunnel.

rbnL2tpTCfgPeerName.name: rbnL2tpTCfgPeerName
rbnL2tpTCfgPeerName.description: This object indicates the remote peer to which this tunnel is connected.

rbnL2tpTCfgTunCtlErrs.name: rbnL2tpTCfgTunCtlErrs
rbnL2tpTCfgTunCtlErrs.description: This object is a count of the number of tunnel control errors encountered by this tunnel.

rbnL2tpTCfgLastCtlErr.name: rbnL2tpTCfgLastCtlErr
rbnL2tpTCfgLastCtlErr.description: The value of the last control error.

rbnL2tpTCfgLastCErrTime.name: rbnL2tpTCfgLastCErrTime
rbnL2tpTCfgLastCErrTime.description: The time of the last control error.

rbnL2tpTCfgTunDataErrs.name: rbnL2tpTCfgTunDataErrs
rbnL2tpTCfgTunDataErrs.description: The number of tunnel data errors.

rbnL2tpTCfgLastDataErr.name: rbnL2tpTCfgLastDataErr
rbnL2tpTCfgLastDataErr.description: The value of the last tunnel data error.

rbnL2tpTCfgLastDErrTime.name: rbnL2tpTCfgLastDErrTime
rbnL2tpTCfgLastDErrTime.description: The time of the last tunnel data error.

rbnL2tpTCfgSessionCount.name: rbnL2tpTCfgSessionCount
rbnL2tpTCfgSessionCount.description: The number of sessions belonging to this tunnel.

rbnL2tpTCfgTotActSessions.name: rbnL2tpTCfgTotActSessions
rbnL2tpTCfgTotActSessions.description: This object indicates the total number of sessions that, at some time, reached the established state.

rbnL2tpTCfgActSessCnt.name: rbnL2tpTCfgActSessCnt
rbnL2tpTCfgActSessCnt.description: This object indicates the total number of sessions that are presently in the established state.

rbnL2tpTCfgTotFailSessions.name: rbnL2tpTCfgTotFailSessions
rbnL2tpTCfgTotFailSessions.description: This object indicates the number of sessions that failed to reach the established state.

rbnL2tpMibTunnelState.name: rbnL2tpMibTunnelState
rbnL2tpMibTunnelState.description: This object is the current state of the tunnel.

rbnL2tpTCfgRemoteTunnelID.name: rbnL2tpTCfgRemoteTunnelID
rbnL2tpTCfgRemoteTunnelID.description: This object indicates the remote tunnel ID. A value of zero indicates that the remote tunnel ID could not be determined.

rbnL2tpTCfgTunnelContext.name: rbnL2tpTCfgTunnelContext
rbnL2tpTCfgTunnelContext.description: This object identifies the context of this tunnel. The empty context name (zero length) indicates that the context could not be determined. Any context name length greater than 80 will be truncated.

rbnL2tpPeerCntEntry.name: rbnL2tpPeerCntEntry
rbnL2tpPeerCntEntry.description: An L2TP Peer Statistics entry. An entry in this table corresponds to a single peer. The statistics reported are the totals for all tunnels that are a part of this peer group.

rbnL2tpPCDataPktSent.name: rbnL2tpPCDataPktSent
rbnL2tpPCDataPktSent.description: This object is a count of the total number of data packets sent through tunnels that are part of this group to the the L2TP peer.

rbnL2tpPCDataPktRx.name: rbnL2tpPCDataPktRx
rbnL2tpPCDataPktRx.description: This object is a count of the total number of data packets received through tunnels that are part of this group from the the L2TP peer.

rbnL2tpPCDataByteSent.name: rbnL2tpPCDataByteSent
rbnL2tpPCDataByteSent.description: This object is a count of the total number of data bytes sent through tunnels that are part of this group to the the L2TP peer.

rbnL2tpPCDataByteRx.name: rbnL2tpPCDataByteRx
rbnL2tpPCDataByteRx.description: This object is a count of the total number of data bytes received through tunnels that are part of this group from the the L2TP peer.

rbnL2tpPCCtlPktSent.name: rbnL2tpPCCtlPktSent
rbnL2tpPCCtlPktSent.description: This object is a count of the total number of control packets sent through tunnels that are part of this group to the the L2TP peer.

rbnL2tpPCCtlPktRx.name: rbnL2tpPCCtlPktRx
rbnL2tpPCCtlPktRx.description: This object is a count of the total number of control packets received through tunnels that are a part of this group from the L2TP peer.

rbnL2tpPCCtlByteSent.name: rbnL2tpPCCtlByteSent
rbnL2tpPCCtlByteSent.description: This object is a count of the total number of control bytes sent through tunnels that are a part of this group to the the L2TP peer.

rbnL2tpPCCtlByteRx.name: rbnL2tpPCCtlByteRx
rbnL2tpPCCtlByteRx.description: This object is a count of the total number of control bytes received through tunnels that are a part of this group from the L2TP peer.

rbnL2tpPCPolicePktDrop.name: rbnL2tpPCPolicePktDrop
rbnL2tpPCPolicePktDrop.description: This object indicates the total number of packets received from L2TP peers of tunnels that are a part of this group that were dropped.

rbnL2tpPCRatePktDrop.name: rbnL2tpPCRatePktDrop
rbnL2tpPCRatePktDrop.description: This object indicates the total number of packets transmitted to the L2TP peers of tunnels in this group that were dropped.

rbnL2tpPCTxSCCRQCnt.name: rbnL2tpPCTxSCCRQCnt
rbnL2tpPCTxSCCRQCnt.description: This object indicates a count of the SCCRQ transmits for this group.

rbnL2tpPCRxSCCRQCnt.name: rbnL2tpPCRxSCCRQCnt
rbnL2tpPCRxSCCRQCnt.description: This object is a count of the received SCCRQ's for this group.

rbnL2tpPCActTunnels.name: rbnL2tpPCActTunnels
rbnL2tpPCActTunnels.description: This object indicates the number of the active tunnels for this group.

rbnL2tpPCTunnelCtlErr.name: rbnL2tpPCTunnelCtlErr
rbnL2tpPCTunnelCtlErr.description: This object indicates the total number of tunnel control errors for all of the tunnels that are a part of this group.

rbnL2tpPCSessionCount.name: rbnL2tpPCSessionCount
rbnL2tpPCSessionCount.description: This object indicates the total number of sessions for this group.

rbnL2tpPCTunnelDataErr.name: rbnL2tpPCTunnelDataErr
rbnL2tpPCTunnelDataErr.description: This object indicates the total number of tunnel data errors reported by members of this group.

rbnL2tpTunnelCntEntry.name: rbnL2tpTunnelCntEntry
rbnL2tpTunnelCntEntry.description: An L2TP Tunnel Statistics entry. An entry in this table corresponds to a single tunnel.

rbnL2tpTCDataPktSent.name: rbnL2tpTCDataPktSent
rbnL2tpTCDataPktSent.description: This object indicates the number of data packets sent from this platform through this tunnel to its peer.

rbnL2tpTCDataPktRcvd.name: rbnL2tpTCDataPktRcvd
rbnL2tpTCDataPktRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of packets received from the L2TP peer for this tunnel.

rbnL2tpTCDataByteSent.name: rbnL2tpTCDataByteSent
rbnL2tpTCDataByteSent.description: This object indicates the number of data bytes sent from this platform through this tunnel to its peer.

rbnL2tpTCDataByteRcvd.name: rbnL2tpTCDataByteRcvd
rbnL2tpTCDataByteRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of data bytes received from the L2TP peer for this tunnel.

rbnL2tpTCCntrlPktSent.name: rbnL2tpTCCntrlPktSent
rbnL2tpTCCntrlPktSent.description: This object indicates the number of control packets sent from this platform through this tunnel to its L2TP peer.

rbnL2tpTCCntrlPktRcvd.name: rbnL2tpTCCntrlPktRcvd
rbnL2tpTCCntrlPktRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of control packets received from the L2TP peer for this tunnel.

rbnL2tpTCCntrlByteSent.name: rbnL2tpTCCntrlByteSent
rbnL2tpTCCntrlByteSent.description: This object indicates the number of control bytes sent from this platform through this tunnel to its L2TP peer.

rbnL2tpTCCntrlByteRcvd.name: rbnL2tpTCCntrlByteRcvd
rbnL2tpTCCntrlByteRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of control bytes received from the L2TP peer of this tunnel.

rbnL2tpTCPolicePktDrop.name: rbnL2tpTCPolicePktDrop
rbnL2tpTCPolicePktDrop.description: This object indicates the number of packets received from the L2TP peer of this tunnel that were dropped.

rbnL2tpTCRatePktDrop.name: rbnL2tpTCRatePktDrop
rbnL2tpTCRatePktDrop.description: This object indicates the number of packets transmitted from this platform through this tunnel that were dropped.

rbnL2tpTCCntrlErr.name: rbnL2tpTCCntrlErr
rbnL2tpTCCntrlErr.description: This object indicate the number of control errors that were detected.

rbnL2tpTCLastCtlErr.name: rbnL2tpTCLastCtlErr
rbnL2tpTCLastCtlErr.description: This object indicates the last control error for this tunnel that was detected.

rbnL2tpTCLastCtlErrTime.name: rbnL2tpTCLastCtlErrTime
rbnL2tpTCLastCtlErrTime.description: This object indicates the time that the last control error for this tunnel was detected.

rbnL2tpTCMaxResendQ.name: rbnL2tpTCMaxResendQ
rbnL2tpTCMaxResendQ.description: This object indicates the maximum length of the resend queue.

rbnL2tpTCMaxUnsentQ.name: rbnL2tpTCMaxUnsentQ
rbnL2tpTCMaxUnsentQ.description: This object indicates the maximum length of the unsent queue.

rbnL2tpTCCurResendQ.name: rbnL2tpTCCurResendQ
rbnL2tpTCCurResendQ.description: This object indicates the current length of the resend queue.

rbnL2tpTCCurUnsentQ.name: rbnL2tpTCCurUnsentQ
rbnL2tpTCCurUnsentQ.description: This object indicates the current length of the unsent queue.

rbnL2tpTCCurWindow.name: rbnL2tpTCCurWindow
rbnL2tpTCCurWindow.description: This object indicates the current window size.

rbnL2tpSessionCntEntry.name: rbnL2tpSessionCntEntry
rbnL2tpSessionCntEntry.description: An L2TP Session Statistics entry. An entry in this table corresponds to a single session.

rbnL2tpMibSessionID.name: rbnL2tpMibSessionID
rbnL2tpMibSessionID.description: This object identifies the Session ID for a given L2TP session.

rbnL2tpSCPktSent.name: rbnL2tpSCPktSent
rbnL2tpSCPktSent.description: This object indicates the number of packets sent by this platform in this session.

rbnL2tpSCPktRcvd.name: rbnL2tpSCPktRcvd
rbnL2tpSCPktRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of packets received by this platform in this session.

rbnL2tpSCByteSent.name: rbnL2tpSCByteSent
rbnL2tpSCByteSent.description: This object indicates the number of bytes sent by this platform in this session.

rbnL2tpSCByteRcvd.name: rbnL2tpSCByteRcvd
rbnL2tpSCByteRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of bytes received by this platform in this session.

rbnL2tpSCMcastPktSent.name: rbnL2tpSCMcastPktSent
rbnL2tpSCMcastPktSent.description: This object indicates the number of multicast packets sent by this platform in this session.

rbnL2tpSCMcastPktRcvd.name: rbnL2tpSCMcastPktRcvd
rbnL2tpSCMcastPktRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of multicast packets received by this platform in this session.

rbnL2tpSCMcastByteSent.name: rbnL2tpSCMcastByteSent
rbnL2tpSCMcastByteSent.description: This object indicates the number of multicast bytes sent by this platform in this session.

rbnL2tpSCMcastByteRcvd.name: rbnL2tpSCMcastByteRcvd
rbnL2tpSCMcastByteRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of multicast bytes received by this platform in this session.

rbnL2tpPeerTunCfgTable.name: rbnL2tpPeerTunCfgTable
rbnL2tpPeerTunCfgTable.description: This table contains objects which identify L2TP peers and tunnels.

rbnL2tpPeerTunCfgEntry.name: rbnL2tpPeerTunCfgEntry
rbnL2tpPeerTunCfgEntry.description: A conceptual row in the rbnL2tpPeerTunCfgTable. An entry in this table corresponds to a single tunnel of a L2TP peer. Entries are added to this table as tunnels become connected. Entries are removed from the table if the communication with one or both ends of a tunnel is lost.

rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteID.name: rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteID
rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteID.description: This object indicates the remote tunnel ID. A value of zero indicates that the remote tunnel ID could not be determined.

rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelLocalNm.name: rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelLocalNm
rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelLocalNm.description: This object indicates the local name that was given to this tunnel. The length of the string will be zero if no local name assigned to the tunnel.

rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteNm.name: rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteNm
rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteNm.description: This object indicates the name that was given to the remote end of this tunnel. The length of the string will be zero if no tunnel name can be obtained from the peer.

rbnL2tpPTCfgPeerLocalNm.name: rbnL2tpPTCfgPeerLocalNm
rbnL2tpPTCfgPeerLocalNm.description: This object identifies the local peer name. The empty peer name (zero length) indicates that the name could not be determined.

rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddrType.name: rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddrType
rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddrType.description: This object identifies the address type contained in rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddr.

rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddr.name: rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddr
rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddr.description: This object identifies the remote IP address for this tunnel (utilized only with User Datagram Protocol).

rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelState.name: rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelState
rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelState.description: This object is the current state of the tunnel.

rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelContext.name: rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelContext
rbnL2tpPTCfgTunnelContext.description: This object identifies the context of this tunnel. The empty context name (zero length) indicates that the context could not be determined. Any context name length greater than 80 will be truncated.

rbnL2tpPTCfgSessionCount.name: rbnL2tpPTCfgSessionCount
rbnL2tpPTCfgSessionCount.description: The number of sessions belonging to this tunnel.

rbnL2tpPTCfgActSessCnt.name: rbnL2tpPTCfgActSessCnt
rbnL2tpPTCfgActSessCnt.description: This object indicates the total number of sessions that are presently in the established state.

rbnL2tpPTCfgTotActSessions.name: rbnL2tpPTCfgTotActSessions
rbnL2tpPTCfgTotActSessions.description: This object indicates the total number of sessions that, at some time, reached the established state.

rbnL2tpPTCfgTotFailSessions.name: rbnL2tpPTCfgTotFailSessions
rbnL2tpPTCfgTotFailSessions.description: This object indicates the number of sessions that failed to reach the established state.

rbnL2tpMibTunnelTrapContext.name: rbnL2tpMibTunnelTrapContext
rbnL2tpMibTunnelTrapContext.description: This object contains the context name to which this tunnel belongs.

rbnL2tpMibTunnelTrapState.name: rbnL2tpMibTunnelTrapState
rbnL2tpMibTunnelTrapState.description: The tunnel state. A value of 1 (true) indicates that a the tunnel is up (in the ESTABLISHED state). A value of 2 (false) indicates that the tunnel is down (no longer in the ESTABLISHED state).

rbnL2tpMibDisableTrap.name: rbnL2tpMibDisableTrap
rbnL2tpMibDisableTrap.description: This object will provide a mechanism for disabling and enabling tunnel traps. A value of 1 (true) indicates that tunnel traps are disabled. A value of 2 (false) indicates that tunnel traps are enabled.

rbnL2tpMibTunnelStateChange.name: rbnL2tpMibTunnelStateChange
rbnL2tpMibTunnelStateChange.description: A rbnL2tpMibTunnelStateChange trap signifies that this particular tunnel has changed state.

rbnL2tpMibTunnelStateChange2.name: rbnL2tpMibTunnelStateChange2
rbnL2tpMibTunnelStateChange2.description: This notification signifies that the SNMP entity has detected that the operational state of a tunnel has entered or moved from the established state. The current tunnel operational state is indicated by the included value of rbnL2tpMibTunnelState.

rbnL2tpMibCompliance.name: rbnL2tpMibCompliance
rbnL2tpMibCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities which implement the L2TP MIB.

rbnL2tpMibCompliance2.name: rbnL2tpMibCompliance2
rbnL2tpMibCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement the Redback L2TP MIB.

rbnL2tpMibPeerCfgGroup.name: rbnL2tpMibPeerCfgGroup
rbnL2tpMibPeerCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects providing peer information of the L2TP protocol, tunnels and sessions.

rbnL2tpMibTunnelCfgGroup.name: rbnL2tpMibTunnelCfgGroup
rbnL2tpMibTunnelCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects providing status and statistics of the L2TP protocol, tunnels and sessions.

rbnL2tpMibPeerCntGroup.name: rbnL2tpMibPeerCntGroup
rbnL2tpMibPeerCntGroup.description: A collection of objects providing peer count statistics.

rbnL2tpMibTunnelCntGroup.name: rbnL2tpMibTunnelCntGroup
rbnL2tpMibTunnelCntGroup.description: A collection of objects providing tunnel count statistics.
